Valid Parentheses Total Accepted: 41274 Total Submissions: 154900 My Submissions Question Solution 
Given a string containing just the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']', determine if the input string is valid.

The brackets must close in the correct order, "()" and "()[]{}" are all valid but "(]" and "([)]" are not.

要 用stack，，左边的进站，碰到右边就看：
                                      1：stack要是空的话，没有东西匹配，返回错
                                      2：pop出第一个和当前的，要是匹配就下一个，
                                      3：最后一定是要保证stack是空的，要是不是空的那就是错的


public class Solution {
    public boolean isValid(String s) {
        if(s.length()==0) return true;
        if(s.length()%2!=0) return false;
        
        Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<Character>();
        
        int n = 0 ;
       
        while(n<s.length()){
            char k = s.charAt(n);
            
           if(k=='(' || k== '[' || k=='{'){
               stack.push(k);
           }else{
             
               if(stack.isEmpty() || k-stack.pop()>3) return false;
               
           }
           n++;
        }
        return stack.isEmpty();
    }
}
